Job Description
JD for SAP BPC:
Develop, modify, and manage Input Forms, Reports, Business Process Flows, Business Logic, Queries for budgeting, forecasting, and financial reporting.
Update and maintain dimensions of BPC databases (i.e. units, unit trees, accounts, account trees, exchange rates, etc.).
Building budget models and maintaining calculations with the budget models*
Develop SAP BPC reports using reporting tools (Business Objects, Business Explorer, etc.) to facilitate seamless drill-through analysis
Configure Data Manager Packages for uploading flat files, InfoProvider data, InfoObject data using Conversion file and transformation files
Communicate and effectively present ideas and solutions to customers, team members, and partners
Provide support for end users of BPC to include management of end user access, monitoring/resolving system performance issues, and uploading data.
Experience in capturing business functional requirements and translating them to technical design.
Should have architecture entire BPC solution
Experience in SDLC processes and team leading abilities.
Excellent articulation and communication skills.
Experience in ABAP and various scripts used in BPC implementations.
